What is the output of the following Python code?
```python
class Shape:
    def __init__(self, name):
        self.name = name
    def area(self):
        return 0

class Circle(Shape):
    def __init__(self, name, radius):
        super().__init__(name)
        self.radius = radius
    def area(self):
        return 3.14 * self.radius * self.radius

c = Circle("MyCircle", 5)
print(c.area())
```

